**who —** The Electron — A fundamental lepton — no known size or structure, a true point particle that behaves as a quantum wave. It is NOT a tiny ball on a track; it exists as a smeared probability cloud around the nucleus.

**what —** A fundamental lepton — no known size or structure, a true point particle that behaves as a quantum wave. It is NOT a tiny ball on a track; it exists as a smeared probability cloud around the nucleus.

**where —** ATM · The Atom  Framework inputs: the Standard Model & atomic/nuclear physics  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** DOES ALL OF CHEMISTRY. The outer electrons form bonds, carry electricity, emit and absorb light, and set the atom's size and shape. Everything you touch, every reaction, every colour — that's electrons rearranging.

**how —** DOES ALL OF CHEMISTRY. The outer electrons form bonds, carry electricity, emit and absorb light, and set the atom's size and shape. Everything you touch, every reaction, every colour — that's electrons rearranging.

